Jennie ROSENBERG, Appellant, v. William I. HEFFRON, Trustee in Bankruptcy for the Estate of Jennie Rosenberg, Bankrupt; Kate A. Bullard and Lloyd Vaughn, Appellees. No. 10174. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. May 27, 1943. L. H. Phillips, of Los Angeles, Cal., for appellant. Thomas S. Tobin, of Los Angeles, Cal., for appellee trustee. Halverson & Halverson and George T. Goggin, by George Halverson, all of Los Angeles, Cal., for appellee Vaughn.

Before GARRECHT, DENMAN, and MATHEWS, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Upon consideration of the transcript of record and briefs filed by respective parties, and oral argument by counsel, ordered motion of appellant for transmittal of evidence denied, and order of District Court affirmed, that a decree be filed and entered accordingly, and that the mandate of this ■Court in this cause issue forthwith.
